#installation instructions
run the espeak-compile.sh script to automatically copy and compile the en_list, en_rules and 
en_extra files. Please make sure you have the latest version of espeak, found at http://espeak.sf.net/test/latest.html.

if sudo privilages are needed, the script will prompt you for a password. If either the directory /usr/share/espeak-data 
is missing or is not a directory, the script will exit with an error.

